data.name: bunifuLabel11.ToolTip
data.value:
When turned on, the browser will click / write / wait using chrome console javascripts instead of selenium. This can be faster and more reliable on slow computers with many streams opened.
Warning: It is technically possible to detect the usage of javascripts within chrome console. Although Riot doesn't have any detection mechanisms against this feature yet, there is always the possibility that they might implement a detection mechanisms against it in the future. As a result, it is recommended to use this feature with caution and at your own risk.

data.name: timeFrameBox.ToolTip
data.value:
The bot can be programmed to stop watching streams during specific hours. This is helpful if you don't want to watch certain streams or if you don't want the bot to watch 24/7.
To set the hours when the bot shouldn't watch streams:
Type "2 - 4" to make the bot stop watching from 2 to 4 o'clock. Or type "2:30 - 4:30" to make the bot stop watching from 2:30 to 4:30. If you want to set multiple time frames, separate them with commas. For example, "2 - 4, 5 - 6, 8 - 10".
Make sure not to put a comma after the last time frame.

data.name: bunifuLabel2.ToolTip
data.value:
Enabling this feature significantly reduces RAM, GPU, and CPU usage, resulting in a smoother experience.
It accomplishes this by removing the stream and all of the content from the streamsite, leaving a blank white browser page. The stream will not be loaded and will not consume any resources. However the JavaScripts on the streamsite, will continue to run in the background, ensuring that you still receive all Drops without issue.
Warning: It is technically possible to detect the local removal of elemets on a webpage. Although Riot doesn't have any detection mechanisms against this feature yet, there is always the possibility that they might implement a detection mechanisms against it in the future. As a result, it is recommended to use this feature with caution and at your own risk.
